01:37:08,088 --> 01:37:10,056
- Yes, thank you. Thank you.
- Thank you.

1141
01:37:10,224 --> 01:37:12,624
I see. Thank you very much.

1142
01:37:14,061 --> 01:37:16,461
Oh, what a day this is going to be.

1143
01:37:17,498 --> 01:37:19,363
- Well, Mrs. Glossop.
- Hello, Egbert.

1144
01:37:19,533 --> 01:37:22,502
Quiet, pl...
Oh, Guy, what are you doing here?

1145
01:37:22,670 --> 01:37:25,969
Oh, Egbert, that's what I've been trying
to remember to tell you about.

1146
01:37:26,140 --> 01:37:28,301
- Oh, was it?
- Yes.

1147
01:37:29,376 --> 01:37:31,344
This is my Mimi.

1148
01:37:31,512 --> 01:37:34,379
Oh, really? Yes. Well, this is my finish.

1149
01:37:34,548 --> 01:37:38,780
- Tonetti, if you have bungled this job...
- Now, <i>scusi, signor,</i> please, <i>scusi.</i>

1150
01:37:38,953 --> 01:37:41,513
Now, Guy, get out.
You're messing up the whole thing.

1151
01:37:41,689 --> 01:37:43,953
- You brought the detectives?
- Better than that.

1152
01:37:44,124 --> 01:37:46,092
I've pulled a supreme coup.
A masterpiece.

1153
01:37:46,260 --> 01:37:47,522
I'll bet this will be good.

1154
01:37:48,229 --> 01:37:50,163
I have brought Mr. Glossop.

1155
01:37:50,331 --> 01:37:51,559
- My husband?
- Yes.

1156
01:37:51,732 --> 01:37:52,960
The husband is coming.

1157
01:37:53,133 --> 01:37:54,828
Shut up, Guy. You've got to get out.

1158
01:37:55,002 --> 01:37:57,971
- No more hiding.
- Oh, please, Guy. You promised.

1159
01:37:58,138 --> 01:38:00,265
All right, I'll hide.

1160
01:38:01,342 --> 01:38:03,776
But please call if you need me.

1161
01:38:05,679 --> 01:38:08,079
- Call anyhow.
- Yes, I will.

1162
01:38:08,249 --> 01:38:11,912
Mimi, it was my idea to have your
husband here. Wasn't it clever of me?

1163
01:38:12,086 --> 01:38:15,715
Oh, Hortense, why did you do that?
Something terrible is liable to happen.

1164
01:38:15,890 --> 01:38:17,881
- Courage, I don't think he'll shoot.
- Shoot?

1165
01:38:18,058 --> 01:38:20,185
Is somebody going to shoot? Let's wait.

1166
01:38:20,361 --> 01:38:24,695
Shoot? Mr. Egbert, never, never have I had
to come in contact with a husband before.

1167
01:38:24,865 --> 01:38:28,426
I don't think it's fair to ask me to do so
now. Where are the detectives?

1168
01:38:28,602 --> 01:38:30,627
I demand the detectives.
It's in my contract.

1169
01:38:30,804 --> 01:38:34,103
I'm sorry. I can't do anything about that.
He's probably on his way up.

1170
01:38:34,275 --> 01:38:37,438
Do something. Do something.
Look amorous. Tonetti, look amorous.

1171
01:38:37,611 --> 01:38:38,908
Hortense, look... Never mind.

1172
01:38:39,079 --> 01:38:41,309
- Come on, come on.
- Yes, Egbert.

1173
01:38:41,482 --> 01:38:44,383
Well, this is too much for Tonetti.

1174
01:38:45,719 --> 01:38:47,209
Quick, quick. What shall we do?

1175
01:38:47,388 --> 01:38:50,789
Well, Mr. Egbert said try
to look amorous. See, like this:

1176
01:38:50,958 --> 01:38:53,426
Oh, you just look sick.

1177
01:38:55,663 --> 01:38:58,029
Well, try this:

1178
01:39:01,135 --> 01:39:02,932
Come in.

1179
01:39:04,004 --> 01:39:06,165
Pardon, madam,
I hope I knocked the right way.

1180
01:39:09,343 --> 01:39:12,870
- Now you've spoiled everything.
- I'm sorry, sir. I came for the dishes.

1181
01:39:13,047 --> 01:39:14,878
Oh, well, the dishes can wait.

1182
01:39:15,049 --> 01:39:17,279
- Can't we do something with him?
- Yes, here.

1183
01:39:17,451 --> 01:39:19,476
- Go quickly there, please.
- Yes, hide him.

1184
01:39:19,653 --> 01:39:21,518
- In the bedroom?
- Yes. Hurry. Hurry.

1185
01:39:21,689 --> 01:39:23,350
- Yes, hurry.
- Oh, now, sir, please...

1186
01:39:23,524 --> 01:39:25,685
- Hi, waiter.
- How do you do, sir?

1187
01:39:25,859 --> 01:39:28,453
- You hiding too?
- Yes, sir. They just shoved me in here.

1188
01:39:28,629 --> 01:39:30,824
Now, once more.

1189
01:39:34,401 --> 01:39:36,164
Come in.

1190
01:39:42,676 --> 01:39:44,439
Oh, Cyril.

1191
01:39:49,883 --> 01:39:51,851
Who is this fellow?

1192
01:39:52,686 --> 01:39:54,017
This is my husband.

1193
01:39:54,188 --> 01:39:57,214
Oh, how do you do?
I'm so very pleased.

1194
01:39:57,758 --> 01:39:59,385
You haven't answered my question.

1195
01:40:00,761 --> 01:40:04,322
I must confess, he's my...

1196
01:40:04,498 --> 01:40:06,693
This object?

1197
01:40:06,867 --> 01:40:11,236
No, I don't believe it.
My dear child, he's nothing to you.

1198
01:40:11,405 --> 01:40:14,806
He has all the earmarks
of a hired corespondent.

1199
01:40:14,975 --> 01:40:20,072
That is not true.
She love me and I love she.

1200
01:40:20,948 --> 01:40:24,816
Mimi, you amuse me.
I'd never believe it with him.

1201
01:40:24,985 --> 01:40:27,977
This...? This hairdresser?

1202
01:40:30,424 --> 01:40:33,791
Guy! Guy!

1203
01:40:34,695 --> 01:40:37,562
I'm sorry to ask you to do this,
but will you kiss me?

1204
01:40:37,731 --> 01:40:40,165
I'm not sorry.

1205
01:40:40,334 --> 01:40:42,666
Bravo. Bravissimo.

1206
01:40:42,836 --> 01:40:45,532
And who, pray, is this new Lothario?

1207
01:40:46,373 --> 01:40:48,864
After the divorce,
we're going to be married.

1208
01:40:49,643 --> 01:40:51,406
What divorce?

1209
01:40:52,379 --> 01:40:54,404
Why, aren't you going to divorce me?

1210
01:40:55,082 --> 01:40:58,779
Why, no, my dear.
I'm going to forgive you.

1211
01:40:58,952 --> 01:41:01,443
Forgive her.

1212
01:41:06,126 --> 01:41:07,491
Enough of this nonsense.

1213
01:41:07,661 --> 01:41:10,061
Mimi, you pack up your things
and come home at once.

1214
01:41:10,230 --> 01:41:13,597
At once, I tell you.
Why, you're just a little lamb who's strayed.

1215
01:41:14,101 --> 01:41:18,197
And you, sir,
are just an ineffectual little puppy.

1216
01:41:21,375 --> 01:41:23,639
At last, I've got my chance
to throw somebody out.

1217
01:41:23,811 --> 01:41:25,938
Oh, no, no, Guy.
You mustn't, please.

1218
01:41:26,213 --> 01:41:29,205
Pardon me, ma'am.
May I go now? I've got my work to do.

1219
01:41:29,383 --> 01:41:30,714
Yes, yes, go ahead.

1220
01:41:30,884 --> 01:41:32,545
Why, how do you do, Professor Brown?

1221
01:41:34,822 --> 01:41:36,449
Professor Brown?

1222
01:41:36,623 --> 01:41:39,183
How are you, professor,
if you don't mind my asking?

1223
01:41:39,359 --> 01:41:42,351
Oh, is this your dear old friend,
the rock thrower?

1224
01:41:42,529 --> 01:41:44,121
Yes, sir, that's him.

1225
01:41:44,698 --> 01:41:47,861
That's ridiculous.
He doesn't know what he's talking about.

1226
01:41:48,035 --> 01:41:50,560
- I never saw this man in my life.
- Oh, come, professor.

1227
01:41:50,737 --> 01:41:54,104
Don't you remember all those little chats
we used to have about rocks?

1228
01:41:54,274 --> 01:41:57,368
You and me and your wife?

1229
01:41:58,579 --> 01:42:00,342
No, I do not.

1230
01:42:00,514 --> 01:42:03,312
And would you know
the professor's wife if you saw her?

1231
01:42:03,484 --> 01:42:04,815
Why, of course I would, sir.

1232
01:42:06,587 --> 01:42:09,420
Am I Mrs. Brown?

1233
01:42:09,590 --> 01:42:12,150
No, ma'am. You're Mrs. Green.

1234
01:42:12,759 --> 01:42:15,250
Well, strike me pink.

1235
01:42:15,429 --> 01:42:21,299
You see, Mrs. Brown, she was French.
She couldn't speak a word of English.

1236
01:42:22,569 --> 01:42:27,597
Why, Buster Brown,
this is most "unfossilish" of you, sir.

1237
01:42:27,774 --> 01:42:29,435
I've got to catch a train.

1238
01:42:29,610 --> 01:42:31,669
- Let me pass, sir.
- I will not, sir.

1239
01:42:31,845 --> 01:42:34,746
- Let me pass, I say.
- Never, sir.

1240
01:42:42,089 --> 01:42:44,182
Well, well, what happened? Did it work?

1241
01:42:44,358 --> 01:42:46,292
Did it work?
Meet the future Mrs. Holden.

1242
01:42:46,460 --> 01:42:49,020
Oh, now... Oh, I told you.
I told you.

1243
01:42:49,196 --> 01:42:50,754
Father will be so proud of me.

1244
01:42:50,931 --> 01:42:53,957
- Egbert and I are going to be married too.
- Yes.

1245
01:42:54,134 --> 01:42:55,863
Why, darling, why, what's the mat...?

1246
01:42:56,036 --> 01:42:58,937
We were married last night,
on our way back from London.

1247
01:42:59,106 --> 01:43:00,937
Last night? Were we?

1248
01:43:01,108 --> 01:43:04,043
Why, of course, sir, we were.
Darling, I'd forgotten about it.

1249
01:43:04,211 --> 01:43:06,577
Isn't it wonderful?
I'll tell you what we'll do.

1250
01:43:06,747 --> 01:43:09,079
We'll hurry back to London
to have a celebration.

1251
01:43:09,249 --> 01:43:12,685
Oh, <i>scusi, scusi,</i> I'm also very good
at parties.

1252
01:45:16,743 --> 01:45:18,734
[ENGLISH]

